You are implementing a Blazor Web App for a logistics company that tracks shipments. The project has already been scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-3dfdb073c300470fbc0fbe04935466d8/ShipmentTracker/` using `dotnet new blazor -o ShipmentTracker -int Auto -ai -au Individual`.

**Project structure:**
- `ShipmentTracker/` - Server project
- `ShipmentTracker.Client/` - Client (WebAssembly) project
- Global Interactive Auto mode - all pages are interactive by default
- ASP.NET Core Identity with SQLite is configured
- `ShipmentTracker/Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs` already has Identity tables

**Architecture rules for Auto mode:**
- All interactive components MUST go in the `.Client` project
- Interactive components cannot access DbContext directly - must use HTTP APIs
- Define service interfaces in `.Client`, implement with HttpClient there
- Implement with direct DB access in server project
- Register matching services in both Program.cs files
- Server data exposed through minimal API endpoints

**What to implement:**

### 1. Shared Models (in `.Client` project)

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Models/ShipmentModels.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public enum ShipmentStatus
{
    Pending,
    PickedUp,
    InTransit,
    OutForDelivery,
    Delivered,
    Cancelled
}

public class ShipmentDto
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public ShipmentStatus Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime ShippedDate { get; set; }
    public DateTime EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public DateTime? ActualDelivery { get; set; }
    public string RecipientName { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public double WeightKg { get; set; }
}

public class UpdateShipmentStatusRequest
{
    public ShipmentStatus NewStatus { get; set; }
}
```

### 2. Service Interface (in `.Client` project)

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/IShipmentService.cs`:
```csharp
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public interface IShipmentService
{
    Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetShipmentsAsync(string? statusFilter = null, string? searchTerm = null);
    Task<ShipmentDto?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber);
    Task<ShipmentDto?> GetShipmentByIdAsync(int id);
    Task<ShipmentDto> CreateShipmentAsync(ShipmentDto shipment);
    Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus newStatus);
}
```

### 3. Client-side HttpClient implementation

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/ShipmentHttpService.cs`:
```csharp
using System.Net.Http.Json;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public class ShipmentHttpService(HttpClient httpClient) : IShipmentService
{
    public async Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetShipmentsAsync(string? statusFilter = null, string? searchTerm = null)
    {
        var query = new List<string>();
        if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(statusFilter)) query.Add($"status={Uri.EscapeDataString(statusFilter)}");
        if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(searchTerm)) query.Add($"search={Uri.EscapeDataString(searchTerm)}");
        var url = query.Count > 0 ? $"/api/shipments?{string.Join("&", query)}" : "/api/shipments";
        return await httpClient.GetFromJsonAsync<List<ShipmentDto>>(url) ?? [];
    }

    public async Task<ShipmentDto?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        var response = await httpClient.GetAsync($"/api/shipments/track/{Uri.EscapeDataString(trackingNumber)}");
        if (!response.IsSuccessStatusCode) return null;
        return await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<ShipmentDto>();
    }

    public async Task<ShipmentDto?> GetShipmentByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        var response = await httpClient.GetAsync($"/api/shipments/{id}");
        if (!response.IsSuccessStatusCode) return null;
        return await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<ShipmentDto>();
    }

    public async Task<ShipmentDto> CreateShipmentAsync(ShipmentDto shipment)
    {
        var response = await httpClient.PostAsJsonAsync("/api/shipments", shipment);
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        return (await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<ShipmentDto>())!;
    }

    public async Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus newStatus)
    {
        var response = await httpClient.PutAsJsonAsync($"/api/shipments/{id}/status", new UpdateShipmentStatusRequest { NewStatus = newStatus });
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
    }
}
```

### 4. Register HttpClient and service in Client Program.cs

Edit `ShipmentTracker.Client/Program.cs` to add:
```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly.Hosting;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

var builder = WebAssemblyHostBuilder.CreateDefault(args);

builder.Services.AddAuthorizationCore();
builder.Services.AddCascadingAuthenticationState();
builder.Services.AddAuthenticationStateDeserialization();

